Package: shinyhubidentity
Title: Read the Signed ShinyHub Identity in a Shiny App
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R:
    person("Ruben J.", "Jongejan", email = "ruben.jongejan@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Verifies the signed identity token that ShinyHub forwards to a
    proxied Shiny app and returns the current user's identity, so apps need no
    JWT plumbing of their own. Every failure mode returns NULL rather than
    erroring, so an app stays testable without SSO.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    jose,
    sodium
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
URL: https://github.com/rvben/shinyhub
BugReports: https://github.com/rvben/shinyhub/issues
